				<div class="postbody">
				It's come to my attention that many people are being swayed to EQ2 because of Blizzards reputation for not cracking down on hackers in games like Diablo and Warcraft...and please correct me if I'm wrong..but the moajority of those games are stored on the client's computer (making hacking incredibly easy)..
<br />

<br />
With WoW being a MMORPG, hopefully they'll follow suit with many other MMORPG and have very few pieces of data clientside....the only real hacks for EQ are run speed, perma EB, no encumberance...etc. These things won't ruin the game for anyone, they won't help you "Slay the dragon!".
<br />

<br />
Am I totally off base by saying that WoW won't be affected as D2 and WC3 are?
<br />

<br />
-aam<br />
